Package fil.project.exceptions

Contains all custom exceptions related to TreeFtp Project error handling
Author:
Adrien Holvoet
  • Exception Summary
    Exception Description
    BadCommandResponseException
    Exception thrown when the socket does not receive a successful response from the FTP server after sending a File Transfer Protocol (RFC 959) command.
    NoDataChannelException
    Exception thrown when it's impossible to create the connection to the data channel.
    SocketNotAcceptedException
    Exception thrown when the socket receives an unknown response when connecting to the FTP Server
    WrongArgumentException
    Exception thrown when there is a bad argument when launching the executable
